I would just like to say to Spatz that noone can forget something as powerful/moving/tramatic/deadly as war. There are MANY men AND women who live with Viet Nam everyday, even 30 years after the fighting has stopped. It is not their choice to be awoken at night to the cries of their dead comrades, I'm sure. They made their choice 30 years ago when they put aside their fear/hopes/dreams/feelings and put on the uniform of the United States of America. The point was made that the soilders you protested are the very same people who gave you the right to protest, life is funny sometimes, isn't it?
